  "provenanceFound": {
    "_": "First observed, in the Biscari collection, by Mommsen. Mommsen considered it to be from Rome, but Korhonen rightly argues that the well attested presence of the Pompeii Sosii in Centuripe and Catania, and the physical form of the epitaph make a Catania - or Centuripe - provenance far more likely. Now in the Museo Civico (sala VII.229, mag. sup.)",
